Package: samplyr
Title: A Tidy Grammar for Survey Sampling
Version: 0.8.9999
Authors@R: person(given = "Ahmadou",
                  family = "Dicko",
                  email = "mail@ahmadoudicko.com",
                  role = c("aut", "cre"),
                  comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-9654-7582"))
Description: Provides a tidy, composable grammar for specifying and executing
    complex survey sampling designs. Supports equal-probability and
    probability-proportional-to-size (PPS) selection, the cube method for
    balanced sampling following Deville and Tillé (2004)
    <doi:10.1093/biomet/91.4.893>, spatially balanced sampling with local
    pivotal and spatially correlated Poisson methods, and controlled category
    counts. Stratified, clustered, multi-stage, and multi-phase designs compose
    through a small set of tidy verbs. Includes sampling frames derived for
    learning and testing from public data for Burkina Faso, Zimbabwe, and
    Kenya.
